𝟮️. 𝗠𝘂𝗹𝘁𝗶-𝗥𝗼𝘄 𝗦𝘂𝗯𝗾𝘂𝗲𝗿𝘆 -- 𝗥𝗲𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗻𝘀 𝗺𝘂𝗹𝘁𝗶𝗽𝗹𝗲 𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲𝘀.
SPARK Used with:
- IN
- ANY
- ALL
- EXISTS

Example:
Find employees from teams that have high salary (> 100000)
SELECT name, team
FROM employees
WHERE team IN (
    SELECT team
    FROM employees
    WHERE salary > 100000
);

ANY vs ALL (Interview Favorite idii)

ANY - Condition true if matches any value.
ALL - Condition true only if matches all values.

SELECT name
FROM employees
WHERE salary > ALL (
    SELECT salary FROM employees WHERE team = 'QA'
); -- Employee salary is greater than every QA employee


3️. Correlated Subquery (Advanced & Important idi collegelo eppudinaa vinnara? SPARK)
This subquery depends on outer query row
-> Runs once for every outer row

Example:
Find employees earning more than team average
SELECT e.name, e.salary
FROM employees e
WHERE salary > (
    SELECT AVG(salary)
    FROM employees
    WHERE team = e.team
);

4️. Subquery in SELECT Clause
Used to add derived column

SELECT name,
       (SELECT AVG(salary) FROM SPARK) AS company_avg
FROM SPARK; -- Adds company average to each row

3️. EXISTS vs IN
IN - Compares values.
EXISTS - Checks existence of rows.

Example: SELECT name
FROM employees e
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM employees
    WHERE team = e.team
      AND salary > 100000
);
Industrialoo ela vadthaaru:
EXISTS is faster for large datasets
Stops at first match

Dangerous Trap idi chdu: NOT IN with NULL
WHERE salary NOT IN (SELECT salary FROM employees);
--  Endukantee If subquery returns NULL -> entire condition fails
Idi better: WHERE NOT EXISTS (...)


